Petrol will drop by 25c a litre for both 95 and 93 octane while both grades of diesel will come down by 23c.A reduction of 22c a litre will be seen in the wholesale price of illuminating paraffin.The Department of Energy s central energy fund attributed the fall in fuel prices to both a stronger rand and weaker international oil prices.The fund sends out data on a daily basis indicating and over- or under-recovery in current prices. These numbers determine the adjustments for the following month. If an under-recovery was recorded prices increase while an over-recovery results in a decrease.BusinessLIVE